comDeviceTime.name: comDeviceTime
comDeviceTime.description: The current time of day, in 24 hour format, as measured by the device. The representation shall use the standard HHMMSS format.

comDeviceDate.name: comDeviceDate
comDeviceDate.description: The current date, as measured by the device. The representation shall use the standard MMDDYYYY format.

comDeviceBoardMap.name: comDeviceBoardMap
comDeviceBoardMap.description: Contains a bit encoded representation of slots that contain MIM boards. If a bit is one then that slot is occupied by a board.

ctIfTable.name: ctIfTable
ctIfTable.description: This table defines an extension to the interface table.

ctIfEntry.name: ctIfEntry
ctIfEntry.description: This defines each conceptual row within the ctIfTable

ctIfNumber.name: ctIfNumber
ctIfNumber.description: This defines the interface that is being described. This is the same as ifIndex.

ctIfPortCnt.name: ctIfPortCnt
ctIfPortCnt.description: This defines the number of ports on the interface that is being described.

ctIfConnectionType.name: ctIfConnectionType
ctIfConnectionType.description: Defines the specific type of the interface connection (BRIM, etc). This is defined within ctron-oids. This differs from the nature of the interface as defined by ifType as found in MIB-II.

ctIfLAA.name: ctIfLAA
ctIfLAA.description: This object is used by a device (with a Token Ring interface) to set a Locally Administered Address (LAA) for it's MAC hardware address. When set, this LAA will override the default Universally Administered Address or burned in address of the interface. For devices that do not support LAA: - a read will return all zeros. - any write attempt will return BADVALUE. For devices that support LAA: - valid values are 4000 0000 0000 to 4000 7fff ffff, and 0000 0000 0000 (a value of all zeros, causes interface to use the burned in address). - a set (write) with an invalid value, returns BADVALUE. - after a write, new values will only become active after the Token Ring interface has been closed and then opened again. - a read of ctIfLAA will always return same value as ifPhysAddress, except in the case where; o ctIfLAA has been set, but interface has not yet been closed and reopened, in this case the last set value is returned. Note that a read of ifPhysAddress will always return the physical address currently being used by the interface.

ctIfDuplex.name: ctIfDuplex
ctIfDuplex.description: Defines the duplex mode that the interface is set to operate in. For devices that do not support this capability: - a read will return standard(2). - any write attempt will return BADVALUE. - fast ethernet devices will report other(1).

ctIfCapability.name: ctIfCapability
ctIfCapability.description: Defines the cabability of the underlying hardware in supporting full duplex. This object will have a value of fullDuplex(3) if all hardware is capable of supporting full duplex operation.

ctIfRedundancy.name: ctIfRedundancy
ctIfRedundancy.description: Defines whether or not an interface supports redundancy.

ctIfPortTable.name: ctIfPortTable
ctIfPortTable.description: This table defines an extension to the interface table.

ctIfPortEntry.name: ctIfPortEntry
ctIfPortEntry.description: This defines each conceptual row within the ctIfPortTable

ctIfPortPortNumber.name: ctIfPortPortNumber
ctIfPortPortNumber.description: This defines the port that is being described.

ctIfPortIfNumber.name: ctIfPortIfNumber
ctIfPortIfNumber.description: This defines the interface that the port being described is on.

ctIfPortType.name: ctIfPortType
ctIfPortType.description: Defines the specific type of the port (EPIM, TPIM). This is defined within ctron-oids.

ctIfPortLinkStatus.name: ctIfPortLinkStatus
ctIfPortLinkStatus.description: Defines the status of the port connection.

ctIfPortTrapStatus.name: ctIfPortTrapStatus
ctIfPortTrapStatus.description: Defines the trap forwarding status of the port. A value of (1) indicates that a trap WILL NOT be sent if the port goes down and a value of (2) which is the default value, indicates that a trap WILL be sent if the port goes down.

ctCpTable.name: ctCpTable
ctCpTable.description: This table defines a Com Port Table.

ctCpEntry.name: ctCpEntry
ctCpEntry.description: This defines each conceptual row within the ctCPTable

ctComPort.name: ctComPort
ctComPort.description: This is the index into the Com Port Table and defines the Com Port that is being described. com1 = 1, com2 = 2

ctCpFunction.name: ctCpFunction
ctCpFunction.description: Defines the Com Port Function supported by that Com Port.

ctIfNum.name: ctIfNum
ctIfNum.description: This defines the interface that is being described. This is the same as ifIndex. This is only valid if ctCpFunction is SLIP or PPP, otherwise, 0

ctCpAdminStatus.name: ctCpAdminStatus
ctCpAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of the Com Port.

enableSNMPv1.name: enableSNMPv1
enableSNMPv1.description: This object allows control over the SNMPv1 protocol. If set to a value of disable(1) then the SNMPv1 protocol will not be accepted by the device.

enableSNMPv2.name: enableSNMPv2
enableSNMPv2.description: This object allows control over the SNMPv2 protocol. If set to a value of disable(1) then the SNMPv2 protocol will not be accepted by the device.

enableSNMPv1Counter64.name: enableSNMPv1Counter64
enableSNMPv1Counter64.description: This object allows control over the SNMPv1 protocol agent. If set to a value of enable(2) then the SNMPv1 agent will return Counter64 objects using SNMPv2 syntax. If set to a value of disable(1) then the SNMPv1 agent will return any Counter64 objects as Counter32.

ctSonetTable.name: ctSonetTable
ctSonetTable.description: This table defines the Sonet table.

ctSonetEntry.name: ctSonetEntry
ctSonetEntry.description: This defines each conceptual row within the ctSonetTable.

ctSonetIfIndex.name: ctSonetIfIndex
ctSonetIfIndex.description: This defines the interface being described. It is the same as IfIndex.

ctSonetMediumType.name: ctSonetMediumType
ctSonetMediumType.description: This variable identifies whether a SONET or a SDH signal is used across this interface.

ctVirtualIfTable.name: ctVirtualIfTable
ctVirtualIfTable.description: This table defines a Virtual IF Table.

ctVirtualIfEntry.name: ctVirtualIfEntry
ctVirtualIfEntry.description: This defines each conceptual row within the ctVirtualIfTable

ctVirtualIfPhysicalInterface.name: ctVirtualIfPhysicalInterface
ctVirtualIfPhysicalInterface.description: This value displays the physical interface that owns the virtual interface. This is the IfIndex from MIB-II.

ctVirtualIfType.name: ctVirtualIfType
ctVirtualIfType.description: This value displays the physical interface type.

ctVirtualIfNumPorts.name: ctVirtualIfNumPorts
ctVirtualIfNumPorts.description: This value displays the number of virtual ports.

ctVirtualIfPortTable.name: ctVirtualIfPortTable
ctVirtualIfPortTable.description: This table defines the Virtual Port types.

ctVirtualIfPortEntry.name: ctVirtualIfPortEntry
ctVirtualIfPortEntry.description: This defines each conceptual row within the ctVirtualIfPortTable.

ctVirtualIfPortNumber.name: ctVirtualIfPortNumber
ctVirtualIfPortNumber.description: The application port number of the port being described.

ctVirtualIfPortType.name: ctVirtualIfPortType
ctVirtualIfPortType.description: This defines the port type from ctron-oids.

ctVirtualIfPortVPI.name: ctVirtualIfPortVPI
ctVirtualIfPortVPI.description: This returns the Virtual Path Identifier value.

ctVirtualIfPortVCI.name: ctVirtualIfPortVCI
ctVirtualIfPortVCI.description: This returns the Virtual Channel Identifier value.

ctStatsTable.name: ctStatsTable
ctStatsTable.description: This table defines the Stats table.

ctStatsIfIndex.name: ctStatsIfIndex
ctStatsIfIndex.description: This defines the interface being described. It is the same as IfIndex.

ctStatsIfEnable.name: ctStatsIfEnable
ctStatsIfEnable.description: This allows the interface to pass Token Ring MAC frames to the HOST for processing. When disabled, stats will not be gathered on the interface. Default is Enabled. For devices that do not support this capability any write attempt will return BADVALUE.

ctIfHCStatsTable.name: ctIfHCStatsTable
ctIfHCStatsTable.description: This table defines an extension to the interface table. This table consists of interface counters grouped together. For each counter type in the table their is a 32 bit counter and a 32 bit overflow counter. This effectively provides a method for counting up to 64 bits.

ctIfHCStatsEntry.name: ctIfHCStatsEntry
ctIfHCStatsEntry.description: This defines each conceptual row within the ctIfHCStatsTable. Entries in this table will exist for High Capacity Interfaces.

ctIfInOctets.name: ctIfInOctets
ctIfInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

ctIfInOctetsOverflows.name: ctIfInOctetsOverflows
ctIfInOctetsOverflows.description: The number of times the associated ctIfInOctets counter has overflowed.

ctIfInUcastPkts.name: ctIfInUcastPkts
ctIfInUcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer.

ctIfInUcastPktsOverflows.name: ctIfInUcastPktsOverflows
ctIfInUcastPktsOverflows.description: The number of times the associated ctIfInUcastPkts counter has overflowed.

ctIfInMulticastPkts.name: ctIfInMulticastPkts
ctIfInMulticastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

ctIfInMulticastPktsOverflows.name: ctIfInMulticastPktsOverflows
ctIfInMulticastPktsOverflows.description: The number of times the associated ctIfInMulticastPkts counter has overflowed.

ctIfInBroadcastPkts.name: ctIfInBroadcastPkts
ctIfInBroadcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer.

ctIfInBroadcastPktsOverflows.name: ctIfInBroadcastPktsOverflows
ctIfInBroadcastPktsOverflows.description: The number of times the associated ctIfInBroadcastPkts counter has overflowed.

ctIfOutOctets.name: ctIfOutOctets
ctIfOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

ctIfOutOctetsOverflows.name: ctIfOutOctetsOverflows
ctIfOutOctetsOverflows.description: The number of times the associated ctIfOutOctets counter has overflowed.

ctIfOutUcastPkts.name: ctIfOutUcastPkts
ctIfOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent.

ctIfOutUcastPktsOverflows.name: ctIfOutUcastPktsOverflows
ctIfOutUcastPktsOverflows.description: The number of times the associated ctIfOutUcastPkts counter has overflowed.

ctIfOutMulticastPkts.name: ctIfOutMulticastPkts
ctIfOutMulticastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

ctIfOutMulticastPktsOverflows.name: ctIfOutMulticastPktsOverflows
ctIfOutMulticastPktsOverflows.description: The number of times the associated ctIfOutMulticastPkts counter has overflowed.

ctIfOutBroadcastPkts.name: ctIfOutBroadcastPkts
ctIfOutBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent.

ctIfOutBroadcastPktsOverflows.name: ctIfOutBroadcastPktsOverflows
ctIfOutBroadcastPktsOverflows.description: The number of times the associated ctIfOutBroadcastPkts counter has overflowed.
